{"ts": "2026-06-08T04:13:49.694064+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Now I have a complete picture of the repository. Here is a summary of the run, build, and preview workflows.\n\n---\n\n## Local Development\n\n**Prerequisites:** Node.js (LTS), Yarn\n\n### Quick start (using the Taskfile)\nThe repo includes a `Taskfile.yaml` with an `init` task that bootstraps everything:\n```bash\ntask init\n```\nThis copies `envs/.env.local` → `.env` and runs `yarn install`.\n\n### Manual setup\n```bash\n# 1. Install dependencies\nyarn install\n\n# 2. Set up environment (dotenv looks for .env first, then falls back to envs/.env.{NODE_ENV})\ncp envs/.env.local .env\n\n# 3. Start the dev server (NODE_ENV=local, listens on all interfaces)\nyarn dev\n```\nThe dev server starts on `http://localhost:10086` (port defined in `envs/.env.local`).  \nHMR is enabled via WebSocket on the same port, and CORS is open.\n\n### Alternative dev command (staging mode)\n```bash\nyarn dev:stg\n```\nUses `envs/.env.stg` (sets `NODE_ENV=stg`, different API base URL).\n\n---\n\n## Building for Different Environments\n\nAll build output goes to the `dist/` directory (configured via `VITE_OUTPUT_DIR`).\n\n| Environment | Command | Mode | Env file used |\n|-------------|---------|------|---------------|\n| **Test / Staging** | `yarn build:stg` | `test` | `envs/.env.stg` |\n| **Production** (Vite mode `prod`) | `yarn build` | `prod` | `envs/.env.prod` |\n| **Production** (Vite mode `production`) | `yarn build:prod` | `production` | `envs/.env.prod` |\n\nEach environment targets a different API base URL (`VITE_APP_BASE_API`) and host (`VITE_HOST`).\n\n---\n\n## Previewing a Build Locally\n\nAfter building, use Vite’s built-in preview server:\n```bash\nyarn serve\n```\nThis serves the `dist/` directory and listens on all interfaces (uses the port from the active env, defaulting to `10086`).\n\n---\n\n## Production Deployment Options\n\n### 1. Docker (Nginx)\nA multi-stage `Dockerfile` is provided:\n```bash\ndocker build -t vite-react-admin .\ndocker run -p 80:80 vite-react-admin\n```\n- **Stage 1:** Node LTS Alpine – installs dependencies and runs `yarn build`.\n- **Stage 2:** Nginx Alpine – copies `dist/` and the custom `nginx.conf`.  \n  The Nginx config handles SPA routing (`try_files … /index.html`) and includes an `/admin` location block.\n\n### 2. Netlify\nThe `netlify.toml` is pre-configured for SPA fallback:\n```toml\n[[redirects]]\n  from = \"/*\"\n  to = \"/\"\n  status = 200\n```\nConnect the repo to Netlify; the build command is `yarn build` and the publish directory is `dist`.\n\n### 3. GitHub Pages\n```bash\nyarn deploy\n```\nUses `gh-pages` to publish the `dist` folder to the repository’s `gh-pages` branch.\n\n---\n\n## Environment Variables Summary\n\n| Variable | `.env.local` | `.env.stg` | `.env.prod` |\n|----------|-------------|-----------|-------------|\n| `NODE_ENV` | `local` | `stg` | `prod` |\n| `VITE_BUILD_ENV` | `development` | `production` | `production` |\n| `VITE_HOST` | `local.lantron.ltd` | `stg.lantron.ltd` | `lantron.ltd` |\n| `VITE_PORT` | `10086` | `10086` | (empty) |\n| `VITE_BASE_URL` | `./` | `./` | `./` |\n| `VITE_APP_BASE_API` | `https://mock.local.lantron.ltd` | `https://mock.stg.lantron.ltd` | `https://mock.lantron.ltd` |\n\n*(The vite config loads these via `dotenv`; it prefers a root `.env` file and falls back to `envs/.env.{NODE_ENV}`.)*", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1959, "prompt_tokens": 13447, "total_tokens": 15406, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 980, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 13184}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 13184, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 263}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-pro", "system_fingerprint": "fp_9954b31ca7_prod0820_fp8_